# Observability Rules

## Prometheus (prom-client)
- All metric names: signal_lab_{name} prefix, snake_case
- Standard labels on scenario counter: type (scenario type), status (success | error)
- Register metrics in MetricsService constructor — never in ad-hoc files
- Expose via GET /metrics using prom-client register.metrics()
- Never create duplicate metric registrations — check registry before adding

## Loki (winston-loki transport)
- Transport config: host from process.env.LOKI_HOST, labels: { app: 'signal-lab' }
- Dynamic labels from log payload: scenarioType maps to a Loki label
- Every log entry must be a structured object — never a plain string
- Required fields on every backend log: scenarioId, scenarioType, status, durationMs
- Log levels: info → success runs, warn → slow_request, error → system_error (and other failures)

## Sentry (@sentry/node)
- Initialize in main.ts before app bootstrap — Sentry.init({ dsn: process.env.SENTRY_DSN })
- Call Sentry.captureException(error) only on system_error scenario type
- Always call after Sentry.init is confirmed — never in a module constructor
- DSN must come from environment variable — never hardcoded

## Grafana dashboard
- Dashboard JSON lives in infra/grafana/dashboards/signal-lab.json
- Provisioned via infra/grafana/provisioning/dashboards/dashboards.yml
- Any new metric added to backend MUST have a corresponding Grafana panel added
- PromQL for rate: rate(signal_lab_scenarios_total[1m]) — not increase()
- Loki panel query: {app="signal-lab"} — always include app label
